name: barcode print
description:
unique barcode prints designed to grow with your child. A cool and funky alternative to display his/her... 

1. name
2. place in the family
3. date of birth 
4. time of birth

choose from six fresh and contemporary colours to suit any interior. 
green/brown/blue/orange/pink/purple

name: blocks - urban
description:
the block seen here is 'pellegrini's'. images 2, 3, 4 and 5 show a selection of urban images to choose from.

beautifully simple, eco plywood image blocks are designed to stand on their own, on your shelf or bench.

each block is hand sanded, oiled and polished to reveal the beautiful detail in the ply edging. images are printed on 100% recycled stock and adhered to block using acid-free glue. the blocks are 110x110mm and 25mm in depth. 

select one and/or make up a set to complete a theme and perhaps mix and match sizes. whatever you decide, blocks will add a little contemporary edge to your home, café, bar or restaurant.

name: luMierebox - australian earthly series
description:
the luMierebox seen here is 'boom!' a native hakea in all her glory. image 2 is 'catching the rain' and image 3 shows the entire australian earthly series.

the luMierebox is a beautifully handcrafted, wax polished plywood timber light box, utilising a selection of recommended images from the gallery. the luMierebox will create an eyecatching and unique ambience in your home, office, café or restaurant. select two or three images and create a visual impact, a sculptural piece by stacking them on top of eachother.

once you’ve purchased one luMierebox, you have the option of purchasing additional prints or add your own if you wish. this allows you to change images to suit any mood in any interior.

now available in two sizes:
small [320x230x90mm] 
large [430x300x90mm]

please note: the luMierebox is only to be used with an 11 watt [or less] energy saving light globe.

please click through all images to view image choices and purchase either the small or large luMierebox from the list below. 

note: shipping within Australia only.

description:
the t.lighthaus© seen here is 'someone's been eating my porridge'. images in this series range from the silver princess in all her stages, the hakea and kangaroo paw. please select images 2 and 3 to view other examples in the range. images 4 and 5 show the entire australian earthly series.

the t.lighthaus© is a photographic translucent lantern designed to house a tealight candle. 205mm in height x 88mm in circumference. lightweight, flat and easy to pack, complete with tabs for easy assembly and instructions enclosed. the t.lighthaus© is also a unique and wonderful gift for loved ones overseas.

name: s/he:
description:
s/he: is a satchel with an element of refinement, finesse and 100% handmade by me.

this 100% dark hardwearing prewashed denim and cotton lined satchel suits both men and women. with no buckles or zips to get in your way, this satchel is deep and folds over to measure 310mm x 230mm. the strap is a 50mm wide seatbelt webbing securely sewn into the bottom seam with a double row of stitching at top. once the satchel is unfolded, a twin pocket at 170mm deep sits on the front panel [hidden when satchel is folded over]. one pocket for your mobile phone, the other for a small notebook, cards, receipts, papers.. etc.

‘she’ is machine stitched on the example shown here but i think it a grand idea if you choose your own special word of up to 6 letters. 

a set of lining fabrics will be selected soon. if you’re interested in a s/he: satchel, please contact me to discuss your preference for lining [be it colour or style]. 

thank you!
m.
